        <h3><a href="/questions/534238/why-hx-x-rho-utxu" class="question-hyperlink">Why $Hx=x-(\rho u^Tx)u$?</a></h3>
        <div class="excerpt">
            A Householder reflection is  a matrix of the form
$$H=I-\rho uu^T$$
with $\rho=2/\|u\|^2$.
Obviously, $Hx=x-\rho uu^Tx$. 

Textbook http://www.mathworks.se/moler/leastsquares.pdf says that 
...
