        <h3><a href="/questions/492817/reflection-along-subspace" class="question-hyperlink">Reflection along subspace</a></h3>
        <div class="excerpt">
            A symmetric space is a Riemannian manifold M with the following property:
For every point $p \in M$ there is an isometry $\phi: M \rightarrow M$
such that $\phi(p) = p$ and $\phi_*(v_p) = -v_p \in ...
